Wash and dry all produce. Preheat oven to 475 degrees. Trim and halve @Brussels Sprouts{16%ounce} lengthwise. Peel and halve @parsnips{12%ounce} lengthwise. Slice into ½-inch half-moons. Cut @sweet potatoes{24%ounce} into ½-inch rounds. Halve @lemon{1}, then cut one half into wedges.

Divide veggies between two #baking sheets{}. Toss with a large drizzle of @olive oil{}, @salt{}, @pepper{}, and a few sprigs of @thyme{¼%ounce}. Roast about ~{12%minutes}, toss, then continue roasting until golden brown, another ~{12-13%minutes}.

Meanwhile, season @chicken breasts{24%ounce} on all sides with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Heat a large drizzle of @olive oil{} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add chicken and cook until browned but not fully cooked through, ~{3-4%minutes} per side.

Transfer chicken to #baking sheets{} with veggies, and finish cooking until no longer pink in the middle, ~{5-8%minutes}.

Add @gluten free chicken demi glace{1}, @water{1%cup}, and a few sprigs of thyme to same pan over medium heat. Bring to a boil, and scrape up any browned bits from bottom of pan. Reduce to a simmer until thickened and reduced by half, ~{3-5%minutes}. Stir in @butter{1%tablespoon}, remove from heat, and stir in juice of half a lemon.

Serve: Discard thyme sprigs. Serve chicken and veggies with pan sauce and lemon wedges. Enjoy!